text: Senokos () is a village in the municipality of Dolneni, North Macedonia.Link to the web site Makedonija It is located 11 kilometers northeast from Prilep. It is divided on three parts. Village is inhabited with Macedonians. ==Demographics== According to the 2002 census, the village had a total of 315 inhabitants.
